name: Samambaia.1
description:
Ferns are pteridophytes, it don't produce flowers or seeds! It reproduce by spores (tiny unicellular structures) and vegetatively (an example is Asplenium rhizophyllum). 
It's a very large group of plants, with great variety (which can be very small -centimeters, or huge - meters) and geographical disposition (abundant in the tropics), the richest place in Ferns is the Amazon Forest, in Brazil.
